Our Solution

Oren is an AI that talks like a human, handles millions of patient calls, records and summarizes every conversation, sends automated emails and reminders, provides actionable insights, creates personalized patient plans, and helps clinics save time — cutting operational workload by up to 68% while boosting efficiency.

Asadbek

Cofounder of Oren

We repeatedly saw clinics struggling with the same issue: patient information arriving fragmented across calls, messages, and forms, leaving care teams to reconstruct critical context under time pressure. This doesn’t just slow operations — it increases uncertainty before appointments even begin. When information is incomplete or unstructured, preparation suffers. As two technical co-founders working closely with clinics, we built Oren to bring structure to patient intake, transform raw interactions into clear, usable summaries, and help clinicians start every visit with the right information in front of them.

Behruz

Founder of Oren

Alongside clinics and care teams, my co-founder has consistently seen how fragmented patient information creates unnecessary pressure before appointments begin. Calls, messages, and forms often capture valuable details, but without structure, that information becomes difficult to use when it matters most. With a strong technical focus, he works on building the systems behind Oren that organize patient input, connect data across touchpoints, and turn raw information into clear, reliable summaries clinicians can review ahead of time. The goal is simple: better preparation, less uncertainty, and more confident care.

Rising Problem

The Healthcare Gap: Rising Bias and Fatal Data Errors (2015–2025)

The Joint Commission

Dr. David Bates

Doctors report that 80% of medical mistakes are caused by miscommunication during the "handoff" from administrative staff to the clinical team. When a receptionist or assistant "edits" or enters data incorrectly—such as a medication dose or a patient's primary complaint—it creates a "hidden" error that the doctor may not catch until after the wrong treatment is administered

Will Oren really save us time on calls and follow-ups?

Absolutely. Oren handles patient calls, records conversations, summarizes key details, and automatically sends follow-ups and reminders. Clinics using Oren can reduce the time spent on routine call management by up to 68%, allowing staff to focus on in-person care and critical tasks, while ensuring no patient is missed.

How accurate is the AI in understanding patients?

Oren uses advanced natural language processing (NLP) to understand patient conversations with over 95% accuracy in recognizing intent and key information. While no AI can replace human judgment entirely, it reliably captures details, summarizes calls, and provides actionable insights that help clinics save time and reduce errors.

Can Oren handle multiple calls at the same time?

Yes. Oren is built to manage millions of calls simultaneously using cloud-based AI infrastructure. Each call is processed independently, ensuring that every patient receives accurate, timely responses. While Oren can handle large volumes, we recommend monitoring peak call times to optimize performance and maintain the highest quality of interaction.

How secure is the patient data recorded by Oren?

Patient data recorded by Oren is protected with enterprise-grade security protocols. All recordings and summaries are encrypted in transit and at rest, complying with international standards such as HIPAA and GDPR. Access is strictly controlled, ensuring that sensitive information is only available to authorized clinic personnel. Oren is designed to provide maximum security without compromising usability or efficiency

What tools do you use?

Oren leverages advanced AI technologies including natural language processing (NLP), machine learning models, cloud-based data processing, and secure database systems. These tools work together to understand patient conversations, summarize key information, automate follow-ups, and provide actionable insights — all in a way that is seamless and reliable for clinic operations.

Can I pause the subscription?

Currently, Oren subscriptions cannot be paused. However, you can cancel at any time and easily reactivate your account later without losing your data. We designed this system to ensure uninterrupted service and maintain continuity of your patient operations.

Can Oren customize conversations for different types of patients?

Yes. Oren can tailor conversations based on patient type, visit reason, or clinic-specific protocols. Using advanced AI and data-driven rules, it adapts responses to ensure interactions are relevant, personalized, and professional, helping clinics provide a more patient-focused experience.
